 discern between violent deaths, heart disease, and cancer.
 Their results come entirely from non-violent deaths.
 In the current study, I double check my results by similarly distinguishing
 non-violent deaths.
 The results are very similar to the main results.
 (Not reported)
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Their results were driven by the mortality rates of African-American women.
\begin_inset Foot
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Specifically, among the African-American population, they found that among
 529 victims treated with a partner arrest, 52, or almost 10% were dead,
 as opposed to only 13 fatalities, or 5%, among the 262 victims whose partners
 were not treated with partner arrest.
 
\end_layout

